1 NOTE Book pp.~82-93. Patriarch of the Cooper family. Of English descent. Came from Pendleton District / Columbia District, S.C. to McMinn County, TN. Received 160-acre land grant Apr.~16, 1825. Will dated Oct. 1838, registered Dec.~10, 1838 (Will
2 CONT Book C pp.~91-93). Signed will with mark (X). Tombstone in Cooper Cemetery: 'Aged 68 yrs.~4 mo.~22 days.' Estate not settled until 1858 (when wife died). Owned slaves named Sam, Clary, Richard, Nance, Margaret, Bob, Cana, Catharine, Kate, Nancy, John.
2 CONT Possibly came from Virginia originally.

