1 NOTE Book p. 74-75. Founder of the Karns family of Knoxville, TN. Native of Virginia; first resided in what is now Grainger County, TN; moved to Knoxville about 1800 (after first moving from Virginia perhaps 1798 to Richland, Grainger Co., Tenn.).
2 CONT Opened a blacksmith shop at NW corner of Main and Water Street, Knoxville. Residence at NE corner of Main and State (two-story frame, razed about 45 years before article). Owned about one acre at corner of State and Main Streets. Bought 100 acres from
2 CONT John White on 27 Nov 1799 (Whites' Mill Creek at present Arlington) for $500; bought 100 more acres adjoining from Robert Houston on 23 Sept 1804. Died 1805 at the old place (Arlington). Name spelled Kerns and Kearns in deed.

